    {
      "block_id": "b332",
      "heading_level": null,
      "index": 332,
      "page": null,
      "spine_index": 9,
      "text": "In a blender, combine 3/4 cup/190 g water with the wheatgrass, dill, parsley leaves, and stock syrup and blend on high until the liquid is pur\u00e9ed, with just small bits of herbs, about 15 seconds. Pass the liquid through a Superbag and skim the foam from the top of the strained liquid. Season with the verjus (you may need a little more or less than the called-for amount) and stir in the parsley pur\u00e9e to thicken the mixture."
    },
